    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The problem is that even if you \"refine\" your algorithms, the creators don't trust a black box. They feel the bias is baked in. The board thinks that adding human moderators—especially a diverse team that understands these cultural nuances—is the only way to restore trust. They believe humans can spot the subtle context that an AI misses. How would you counter the argument that a diverse human team is actually more \"fair\" than your current system?",
